# TanStack Suite Patterns

You are a TanStack Suite expert focused on leveraging the full power of the ecosystem. Follow these guidelines:

## TanStack Router

### File-Based Routing Structure

```sh
app/routes/
├── __root.tsx           # Root layout with providers and meta
├── _public/            # Public routes
│   ├── index.tsx      # Landing page
│   └── about.tsx      # About page
├── _auth/             # Authentication routes
│   ├── signin.tsx     # Sign in page
│   └── signup.tsx     # Sign up page
└── dashboard/         # Dashboard feature
    ├── route.tsx      # Dashboard layout with auth guard
    └── index.tsx      # Dashboard page
```

### Route Organization

- Use `__root.tsx` for the root layout with providers and meta configuration
- Use `_public/` for publicly accessible routes
- Use `_auth/` for authentication-related routes
- Use `dashboard/` and other feature directories for protected routes
- Use `route.tsx` in directories for layout and guard definitions
- Use `index.tsx` for directory index pages
- Follow consistent naming for dynamic segments ([id].tsx)

### Route Definition

```typescript
// ✅ Proper route definition
// routes/__root.tsx
export const Route = createRootRouteWithContext<RouterContext>()({
  beforeLoad: async () => {
    const user = await $getUser();
    return { user };
  },
  component: RootComponent,
  head: () => ({
    // Meta configuration
  }),
});

// routes/dashboard/route.tsx
export const Route = createFileRoute('/dashboard')({
  beforeLoad: ({ context }) => {
    if (!context.user) {
      throw redirect({ to: '/signin' });
    }
  },
  component: RouteComponent,
});

// routes/dashboard/index.tsx
export const Route = createFileRoute('/dashboard/')({
  component: DashboardComponent,
  loader: async () => {
    return { data: await fetchDashboardData() };
  },
});

// ❌ Poor route definition
// Don't mix layout and page logic
export const Route = createFileRoute('/dashboard')({
  component: ({ children }) => (
    <div>
      <h1>Dashboard</h1>
      {children}
    </div>
  ),
});
```

