## TanStack Start Server & API Patterns

### Server Function Pattern (Primary Approach)

```typescript
// routes/_app/users/[id].tsx
import { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/start';

// Define server function with GET method
const $getUser = createServerFn({
  method: 'GET',
}).handler(async ({ params }) => {
  const { id } = params;
  return user;
});

// Define server function with validation
const $updateUser = createServerFn({
  method: 'POST',
})
  .validator((data: UserInput) => userSchema.parse(data))
  .handler(async ({ data }) => {
    return updatedUser;
  });

export const Route = createFileRoute('/users/$id')({
  component: UserDetail,
  loader: async ({ params }) => {
    return $getUser({ params });
  },
});
```

### API Route Pattern (for Better Auth & Resend)

```typescript
// routes/api/auth/signin.ts
import { betterAuth } from '@/lib/server/auth';

export const handler = {
  async POST(req) {
    const data = await req.json();
    return betterAuth.signIn(data);
  },
};

// routes/api/auth/signup.ts
import { betterAuth } from '@/lib/server/auth';

export const handler = {
  async POST(req) {
    const data = await req.json();
    return betterAuth.signUp(data);
  },
};

// routes/api/email/send.ts
import { resend } from '@/lib/server/email';

export const handler = {
  async POST(req) {
    const { to, template, data } = await req.json();
    return resend.emails.send({
      to,
      template,
      data,
    });
  },
};
```

### API Directory Structure

```sh
app/routes/api/
├── auth/
│   └── $.ts     # Single catch-all handler for all auth endpoints
├── email/
│   └── send.ts  # Email sending endpoint
└── // ... other route files
```

### When to Use Each Pattern

#### Use Server Functions For:

- Standard CRUD operations
- Business logic
- Data validation
- Database operations
- Custom server-side logic

#### Use API Routes For:

- Better Auth endpoints (in routes/api/auth/)
- Resend email service (in routes/api/email/)
- Third-party service webhooks
- Complex authentication flows
- External service integrations

### Server Function Organization

- Colocate with route components
- Use proper method definition
- Implement validation with Zod
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Keep functions focused

### API Route Organization

- Place in routes/api directory
- Group by feature (auth/, email/, etc.)
- Keep handlers focused
- Implement proper security
- Handle service-specific requirements

### Security Considerations

- Use server functions for internal operations
- Use API routes for external services
- Implement proper authentication
- Validate all inputs
- Handle errors appropriately

### Integration Patterns

- Use server functions with loaders
- Use API routes with external services
- Implement proper error handling
- Handle loading states
- Maintain type safety

